If my serving in Congress is necessary to ensure my children have a brighter future, then that's a sacrifice I'm willing to make #ar4 #arpx
"I am a lifelong resident of Garland County…. It has never been my life ambition to live and work in Washington, DC." #ar4 #arpx #argop
1/2 "Liberals in Washington and here in Arkansas talk about “progressive” reforms when they discuss their agenda." #ar4 #arpx #argop
2/2 "But the only “progression” I see is away from our individual rights and liberties" #ar4 #arpx #argop
2/2 "I couldn’t wait around to be asked my opinion—this was too big of a deal." #ar4 #arpx #argop
1/2 "I knew that when I went to the floor to speak against the Private Option, I was painting a target on myself." #ar4 #arpx #argop
1/2 "...my covenant was not with the state agencies or the lobbying firms looking to spend the free money from Washington" #ar4 #arpx #argop
2/2 "my covenant is with the hardworking Arkansas taxpayers who know that every $ gov takes out their pocket is not free" #ar4 #arpx #argop
1/2 "As you know, I stood in opposition to the Private Option plan. It was supported by many of my Republican friends." #ar4 #arpx #argop
2/2 "Because of my desire to solve problems and work through issues, I helped write some of the plan." #ar4 #arpx #argop
Sharon Westerman introducing @Bruce_Westerman today. #ar4 #argop #arpx http://t.co/AxJj05uoNv
3/3 "I have no doubt we can move forward." #ar4 #arpx #argop
2/3 "Or, do we go backwards to the days when Barack Obama and Nancy Pelosi ran roughshod over Congress?" #ar4 #arpx #argop
1/3 "Do we continue to move forward in our fight against the unfair government in Washington?" #ar4 #arpx #argop
1/4 "There are questions that are at the crux of the 2014 campaign: Can we make government treat us fairly?" #ar4 #arpx #argop
3/4 "instead of being forced to live by rules that demand equality of outcome?" #ar4 #arpx #argop
2/4 "Can we move forward to a time where we have equality of opportunity" #ar4 #arpx #argop
